page.title: 15Life in Tourist Dedham
page.content: Dedham is a very beautiful village so lots of people from all over the world come here. I live in Royal Square in a 500yr old house between the hair _ dresser and the Marlborough Head. When we go out in our car six cars are waiting for our space. When we return we often have to park a long way away and move the car later. Coaches are worse; they take four spaces or else park beside you, blocking you in. If we forget to lock our door people walk in and ask if we are serving dinner. They are not so keen when they hear it is fish fingers. They even go upstairs looking for the hairdressers or ask if they can use the toilet. Even so it is handy living in the High Street. If you want a Mars bar you can go across to the shop and get one. If the shop is not full of tourists.
